’Щ@b40c75a6807c717d4c912322c64339c56bccd82a69b4fab783ece2dce1e68a7dЪ0Title: title: module
Path: Examples
Content:
Define a custom command in a module and call it.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> module spam { export def foo [] { "foo" } }; use spam foo; foo
foo

```
Define an environment variable in a module.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> module foo { export-env { $env.FOO = "BAZ" } }; use foo; $env.FOO
BAZ

```
Define a custom command that participates in the environment in a module and call it.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> module foo { export def --env bar [] { $env.FOO_BAR = "BAZ" } }; use foo bar; bar; $env.FOO_BAR
BAZ

```
